## Background
Python FastMCP v2.14.4 supports icons on tools, resources, and prompts for visual representation in UIs. Icons are optional metadata with three possible fields:
- src: URL or data URI
- mimeType: MIME type (image/png, image/svg+xml, etc.)
- sizes: Size hints (e.g., "32x32", "64x64")

## Requirements

### Protocol Types (fastmcp-protocol)
Add Icon struct and icon field to components:
```rust
/// Icon metadata for visual representation
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, Default, PartialEq)]
#[serde(rename_all = "camelCase")]
pub struct Icon {
    /// URL or data URI for the icon
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub src: Option<String>,
    /// MIME type of the icon
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub mime_type: Option<String>,
    /// Size hints (e.g., "32x32")
    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
    pub sizes: Option<String>,
}
```

Add to Tool, Resource, Prompt:
```rust
#[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]
pub icon: Option<Icon>,
```

### Server Handler Traits
Add `fn icon(&self) -> Option<&Icon>` to handler traits with default None impl

### Macro Support
Add `icon = "url"` or `icon(src = "url", mime_type = "image/png")` attribute

## Implementation Approach

1. Define Icon struct in fastmcp-protocol/src/types.rs
2. Add icon field to Tool, Resource, Prompt, ResourceTemplate
3. Add icon() method to handler traits
4. Update Router to store icon metadata
5. Update macros to parse icon attributes

## Files to Modify
- crates/fastmcp-protocol/src/types.rs
- crates/fastmcp-server/src/router.rs
- crates/fastmcp-server/src/handler.rs
- crates/fastmcp-macros/src/lib.rs

## User Experience Considerations
- Support both simple URL string and full Icon struct in macros
- Validate URL format (http/https/data URI)
- Support common image MIME types with auto-detection from extension
- Size hints should follow standard format (WxH)

